Tests for the quickstream software package

At the start of the project the API is unstable, so at the start we tend
to use the one program "quickstream" to run and test different parts of
the API.  Had we wrote C code here to test different parts of the API,
than we'd have more programs/code to change if the API changes.  The
program "quickstream" can be used to test many parts of the API, though
the test winds up aggregating more code, having less code to change if the
API changes is a better trade-off.

